# Deobfuscated Code

Let me work through this step by step.

## Step 1: Resolve the string table

The obfuscator encrypts strings into a base64-like lookup table. The function `a0_0x3e56` decodes entries from the array `a0_0x111f()` using a base64 decoder with XOR rotation. After resolving all the hex indices to their decoded strings, and applying the author's corrections from the blog post (where deliberately misleading physics names were substituted), here's the clean version:

```javascript
// ─── Constants ───
const TAU = 6.283;          // 2π
const PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
const SQRT1_2 = 0.707;      // √(1/2)

// ─── Physics Parameters ───
// (Names corrected per the author's "Panda-Gibbon Papers" blog post)
const physics = {
  repulsion: 4000,           // obfuscated as "attraction" — Coulomb-like repulsion between all nodes
  springCoeff: 0.004,        // obfuscated as "frictionCoeff" — default spring stiffness for edges
  damping: 0.92,             // obfuscated as "amplification" — velocity decay per tick (friction)
  centerGravity: 0.0003,     // obfuscated as "dispersal" — gentle pull toward canvas center
  maxParticles: 40,          // obfuscated as "inertiaCore" → actually max particle count
  streamDecay: 0.04,         // particle stream friction factor
  theta: 0.06               // camera smoothing interpolation factor
};

// ─── Nodes ───
// Each node: { id, label, r (radius), x, y, vx, vy }
const nodes = [
  { id: "hub",      label: "Hub",      r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "alpha",    label: "Alpha",    r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "beta",     label: "Beta",     r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "gamma",    label: "Gamma",    r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "delta",    label: "Delta",    r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "epsilon",  label: "Epsilon",  r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// ─── Edges (springs) ───
// Each edge: { a, b, rest (rest length), k (spring constant) }
const edges = [
  { a: "hub", b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
  { a: "hub", b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
  { a: "hub", b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "hub", b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "hub", b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// ─── Camera state ───
let camera       = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };   // current (smoothed)
let cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };   // target

// ─── Particles (decorative sparks emitted from nodes) ───
let particles = [];
let tick = 0;

// ─── Helper: find node by ID ───
function findNode(id) {
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}

// ─── Core physics step ───
function simulate() {

  // 1) Coulomb repulsion — every pair of nodes pushes each other apart
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      const dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      const dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
      const force = physics.repulsion / (dist * dist);   // inverse-square
      const fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      const fy = (dy / dist) * force;
      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // 2) Spring (Hooke) forces along each edge
  for (let i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
    const a = findNode(edges[i].a);
    const b = findNode(edges[i].b);
    if (!a || !b) continue;

    const dx = b.x - a.x;
    const dy = b.y - a.y;
    const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    const displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
    const force = (edges[i].k || physics.springCoeff) * displacement;

    a.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    a.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    b.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    b.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // 3) Per-node: center gravity, damping, position integration
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    // Gentle pull toward canvas center (400, 300)
    nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * physics.centerGravity;
    nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * physics.centerGravity;

    // Velocity damping (multiply by 0.92 → reduces speed each frame)
    nodes[i].vx *= physics.damping;
    nodes[i].vy *= physics.damping;

    // Euler integration — update positions
    nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
    nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
  }
}

// ─── Spawn a decorative particle from a random node ───
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= physics.maxParticles) return;

  const source = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  const angle  = Math.random() * TAU;
  const speed  = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;

  particles.push({
    x: source.x,
    y: source.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,    // frames to live
    size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * PHI) * SQRT1_2
  });
}

// ─── Update all particles (move, decay, cull) ───
function updateParticles() {
  for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    const p = particles[i];
    p.age++;

    // Friction on particle velocity
    p.vx *= (1 - physics.streamDecay * 0.125);
    p.vy *= (1 - physics.streamDecay * 0.125);

    // Move
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;

    // Remove expired particles
    if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);
  }
}

// ─── Smooth camera interpolation toward target ───
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x    += (cameraTarget.x    - camera.x)    * physics.theta;
  camera.y    += (cameraTarget.y    - camera.y)    * physics.theta;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom)  * physics.theta;
}

// ─── Main loop tick (called every 16 ms ≈ 60 fps) ───
function step() {
  simulate();
  updateParticles();
  updateCamera();

  // Spawn a new particle every 3rd tick
  if (tick % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
  tick++;
}

setInterval(step, 16);
```

---

## What it does — summary

This is the **physics engine** (no rendering) for a **force-directed graph visualization**:

| System | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Repulsion** | Every node pair repels via inverse-square force (like charged particles), preventing overlap |
| **Springs** | Connected nodes are linked by Hooke's-law springs with individual rest lengths and stiffnesses, pulling them toward equilibrium distances |
| **Center gravity** | A weak constant force pulls all nodes toward (400, 300) so the graph doesn't drift off-screen |
| **Damping** | Each frame, velocities are multiplied by 0.92, draining kinetic energy so the system settles |
| **Particles** | Decorative sparks spawn from random nodes, drift outward with slight friction, and fade out after 800–2000 frames — purely cosmetic |
| **Camera** | Smooth exponential interpolation (lerp factor 0.06) moves the viewport toward a target position/zoom |
| **Main loop** | `setInterval` at 16ms drives the simulation; particles spawn every 3rd tick |

The graph has a **hub-and-spoke topology**: a central "Hub" node connected to five satellite nodes (Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon), with a few cross-links (Alpha↔Beta, Gamma↔Delta, Alpha↔Epsilon). The rendering code (which draws this to a Canvas) is presumably in a separate file.
